Definition: completely prepared or in condition for immediate action or use or progress
Example: get ready; she is ready to resign; the bridge is ready to collapse; I am ready to work; ready for action; ready for use; the soup will be ready in a minute; ready to learn to read
Synonyms: noun, state, ready, readiness, UNREADY, PREPARED, WILLING, completely, prepared, or, in, condition, for, immediate, action, use, progress, get, she, is, to, resign, the, bridge, collapse, I, am, work, soup, will, be, a, minute, learn, read
Category: adj.all
